leadingComments.value: * * Computes a cycle decomposition of an input permutation. This algorithm is * deterministic; the algorithm will procedes in a sequential manner, first * yielding the cycle containing the first (in input order) index of the * permutation, then yielding the cycle containing the first (in input order) * index of the permutation that is not in the first cycle, etc. The output is * in the form of an iterator over cycles [a, [b, c, ...]] where * a is the first element of the cycle and the list [b, c, * ...] contains the second, third, etc. elements of the cycle. The * algorithm uses an helper array to remember which elements have already been * encountered. * * @see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permutation#Cycle_notation * * @param {Array} sigma The input permutation. * @param {Array} used The helper array. * @returns {IterableIterator} The cycles [a, [b, c, ...]] for sigma.
